lete the cohort and get your full course fee reimbursed. Terms and conditions apply."})]}),d.jsx(ht,{to:"/reimburse",children:d.jsxs(Le,{className:"cursor-pointer rounded-none rounded-tr-lg rounded-bl-lg border border-transparent bg-neutral-900 whitespace-nowrap text-white transition-colors duration-200 hover:bg-black/90 dark:bg-white dark:text-black",size:"lg",children:["Learn More ",d.jsx(Ut,{className:"-ml-1","aria-hidden":!0})]})})]})})})}const Eoe=[{id:"phase-1",title:"System Design Fundamentals",description:"This phase lays the foundation of system design by starting extremely small (a system for a single user) and gradually understanding where complexity naturally emerges.",topics:[{id:"phase-1-topic-1",title:"Core Concepts",subtopics:[{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-1",title:"How Internet works and DNS Magic"},{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-2",title:"The Request Response Cycle and Server Client Architecture"},{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Designing a system for ONE user and gradually scaling to 10 users"},{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Understanding the Application Layer and Data Layer"},{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Problems when going from just ONE user to 10 users"}]}]},{id:"phase-2",title:"Scaling to Thousands of Users & Beyond",description:`Now that we've handled the basics, next phase is all about handling traffic, concurrency, and distribution. This is where your systems need to stop being "toy projects" and start acting like production-grade architectures.`,topics:[{id:"phase-2-topic-1",title:"Scaling Strategies",subtopics:[{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-1",title:"Application-level scaling (horizontal vs vertical)"},{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Data-layer scaling (sharding and replication)"},{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Microservices and Monolith Architecture - trade-offs and pitfalls"},{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Single points of failure and system bottlenecks"},{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Consistency in distributed systems (CAP theorem in real life)"},{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-6",title:"Caching 101"}]}]},{id:"phase-3",title:"Synchronous & Asynchronous Patterns",description:"Now that we know about scalings and caching, let's understand the most important thing that makes your system robust and scale to millions of users.",topics:[{id:"phase-3-topic-1",title:"Async Architecture",subtopics:[{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-1",title:"The Sync and Async Programming Patterns"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Async Patterns in Microservice Architecture"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Async Processing Patterns: queues, pub/sub, and event-driven designs"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Message Queues: single vs distributed queues, priority handling"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Pub/Sub vs Event Driven vs Queues: When to use what?"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-6",title:"Fan-Out Architectures: scaling event-driven systems"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-7",title:"CQRS - Command Query Responsibility Segregation"}]}]},{id:"phase-4",title:"From Local Development to Production",description:'Until now, everything runs on localhost and this is the phase where things get to start serious. The "Money" part gets involved here, and this is where your system design can decide if you are going to have a Pizza party this weekend or not.',topics:[{id:"phase-4-topic-1",title:"Production Infrastructure",subtopics:[{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-1",title:"Cloud infrastructures - AWS, Digital Ocean, etc."},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-2",title:"CDNs (Content Delivery Networks) - bringing data closer to users"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Load Balancers and traffic distribution"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Understanding meaning behind CPU and Memory"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Cost related to CPUs and Memory"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-6",title:"Virtual Private Clouds (VPCs)"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-7",title:"Public IP and Private IP addressing"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-8",title:"Bad Boys do DDoS"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-9",title:"When to Scale Out and Scale In?"}]}]},{id:"phase-5",title:"Database Architecture & Design",description:"Databases are the heart of any system. They determine scalability, reliability, and performance.",topics:[{id:"phase-5-topic-1",title:"Database Fundamentals",subtopics:[{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-1",title:"What is a Database really is?"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Why not just use files?"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Relational vs non-relational databases"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Key-Value Stores: simplicity at speed"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Choosing the Right Database"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-6",title:"The paradigm shift toward real-time databases"}]}]},{id:"phase-6",title:"Cloud Native System Design [AWS]",description:"In this phase, we will be discussing core AWS services which helps you to scale your system with managed service. No, AWS is not sponsoring us for this as of now, Maybe in future.",topics:[{id:"phase-6-topic-1",title:"AWS Services",subtopics:[{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-1",title:"Core AWS Services"},{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-2",title:"AWS EC2, ECS, and Lambda: compute at scale"},{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-3",title:"RDS, DynamoDB, and Aurora: managed database options"},{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-4",title:"API Gateway + Load Balancers: managing traffic in the cloud"},{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-5",title:"S3 and CloudFront: storage + global content delivery"},{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-6",title:"Monitoring and Observability using CloudWatch"}]}]},{id:"phase-7",title:"Real-time Systems Design",description:"System design varies significantly based on application requirements. This phase focuses on real-time systems such as video conferencing and live streaming platforms like zoom and discord.",topics:[{id:"phase-7-topic-1",title:"Real-time Technologies",subtopics:[{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-1",title:"TCP vs UDP and why WebRTC uses UDP"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-2",title:"WebRTC vs traditional socket-based communication"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Common WebRTC architectural patterns"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Peer-to-peer vs MCU vs SFU architectures"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-5",title:"System design of an SFU (Mediasoup)"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-6",title:"How live streaming works: YouTube Live, RTMP, OBS, and FFmpeg"}]}]},{id:"phase-8",title:"Architecting AI-Powered Systems",description:"AI is the new protein, You just find it everywhere, but not sure what to do with it?",topics:[{id:"phase-8-topic-1",title:"AI System Architecture",subtopics:[{id:"phase-8-topic-1-sub-1",title:"RAG Pipelines"},{id:"phase-8-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Large context management strategies"},{id:"phase-8-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Vector databases alongside traditional application databases"},{id:"phase-8-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Workflows Engines - The queue system for AI Applications"},{id:"phase-8-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Real-time AI applications, including voice-based AI systems"}]}]},{id:"phase-9",title:"Cracking System Design Interviews",description:"This phase brings everything together. You will learn not only how to design systems, but how to clearly communicate your decisions during interviews.",topics:[{id:"phase-9-topic-1",title:"Interview Preparation",subtopics:[{id:"phase-9-topic-1-sub-1",title:"System Design Interviews - mindset and strategy"},{id:"phase-9-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Authentication and Authorization (Google Zanzibar model)"}]},{id:"phase-9-topic-2",title:"Classic Design Challenges",subtopics:[{id:"phase-9-topic-2-sub-1",title:"Rate Limiter"},{id:"phase-9-topic-2-sub-2",title:"Consistent Hashing"},{id:"phase-9-topic-2-sub-3",title:"Key-Value Store"},{id:"phase-9-topic-2-sub-4",title:"URL Shortener"},{id:"phase-9-topic-2-sub-5",title:"YouTube, Netflix, and Hotstar system designs"},{id:"phase-9-topic-2-sub-6",title:"Hotel reservation systems and the double-booking problem"}]}]},{id:"bonus",title:"Bonus",description:"Extra rewards for curious minds.",topics:[{id:"bonus-topic-1",title:"Perks",subtopics:[{id:"bonus-topic-1-sub-1",title:"Bounties"},{id:"bonus-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Giveaways"},{id:"bonus-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Hands-on Workshops"},{id:"bonus-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Live Interactive Quizzes"},{id:"bonus-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Guest Lectures"},{id:"bonus-topic-1-sub-6",title:"Resume + Portfolio Guidance"}]}]}],Aoe=[{id:"phase-0",title:"React JS Refresher",description:"This phase strengthens your React foundation so you can transition smoothly into mobile development with confidence and clarity.",topics:[{id:"phase-0-topic-1",title:"React Fundamentals",subtopics:[{id:"phase-0-topic-1-sub-1",title:"What is React"},{id:"phase-0-topic-1-sub-2",title:"SPA vs traditional websites"},{id:"phase-0-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Component-based architecture"},{id:"phase-0-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Virtual DOM fundamentals"}]},{id:"phase-0-topic-2",title:"Project Structure & Syntax",subtopics:[{id:"phase-0-topic-2-sub-1",title:"Folder structure for scalable React apps"},{id:"phase-0-topic-2-sub-2",title:"JSX fundamentals"},{id:"phase-0-topic-2-sub-3",title:"Functional components"},{id:"phase-0-topic-2-sub-4",title:"Props and component composition"}]},{id:"phase-0-topic-3",title:"Hooks & Forms",subtopics:[{id:"phase-0-topic-3-sub-1",title:"useState, useEffect, useRef, useCallback"},{id:"phase-0-topic-3-sub-2",title:"Event handling in React"},{id:"phase-0-topic-3-sub-3",title:"Controlled vs uncontrolled inputs"},{id:"phase-0-topic-3-sub-4",title:"Handling forms properly"}]}]},{id:"phase-1",title:"Getting Started with Expo",description:"This phase introduces modern mobile development using React Native and Expo. You'll understand how cross-platform apps are structured and how the development workflow works when building applications that run on real devices.",topics:[{id:"phase-1-topic-1",title:"Expo Basics",subtopics:[{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-1",title:"What is Mobile Development?"},{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-2",title:"What is React Native & Expo"},{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Environment setup & first Expo app"},{id:"phase-1-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Understanding project structure"}]}]},{id:"phase-2",title:"Core Components & Styling",description:"Now that your environment is ready, this phase focuses on building mobile interfaces using core components and responsive styling techniques that adapt across devices and screen sizes.",topics:[{id:"phase-2-topic-1",title:"Core Components",subtopics:[{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-1",title:"View, Text, Image, TextInput"},{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Pressable, ScrollView, Button, Switch"},{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-3",title:"FlatList, KeyboardAvoidingView"},{id:"phase-2-topic-1-sub-4",title:"ImageBackground, TouchableOpacity"}]},{id:"phase-2-topic-2",title:"Styling",subtopics:[{id:"phase-2-topic-2-sub-1",title:"StyleSheet (Create, Compose, Flatten)"},{id:"phase-2-topic-2-sub-2",title:"Responsive Design Techniques"},{id:"phase-2-topic-2-sub-3",title:"useColorScheme (Dark/Light Mode)"},{id:"phase-2-topic-2-sub-4",title:"useWindowDimensions"}]}]},{id:"phase-3",title:"Navigation with React Navigation",description:"Mobile apps rely heavily on navigation flows. In this phase, you'll learn how real applications structure screen transitions and organize multi-screen experiences.",topics:[{id:"phase-3-topic-1",title:"React Navigation",subtopics:[{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-1",title:"Setup & configuration"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Screen navigation"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Passing parameters"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Stack Navigation (customization)"},{id:"phase-3-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Bottom Tabs & Drawer Navigation"}]}]},{id:"phase-4",title:"Expo Router (Modern Routing)",description:"This phase introduces file-based routing used in modern Expo applications and helps structure navigation in scalable and production-ready ways.",topics:[{id:"phase-4-topic-1",title:"Expo Router",subtopics:[{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-1",title:"File-based routing fundamentals"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Static routes"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Dynamic routes [id]"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Groups (auth)"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-5",title:"_layout.tsx and nested layouts"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-6",title:"+not-found"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-7",title:"+middleware"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-8",title:"Protected routes & stacks"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-9",title:"Tabs (JS, Native, Custom)"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-10",title:"Drawer Navigation"},{id:"phase-4-topic-1-sub-11",title:"Splash Screens & App Icons"}]}]},{id:"phase-5",title:"Networking & Backend Integration",description:"Now that your application structure is ready, this phase connects your mobile app with backend services and teaches how real applications exchange data with servers.",topics:[{id:"phase-5-topic-1",title:"API & Backend",subtopics:[{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-1",title:"API fundamentals"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Creating API routes"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-3",title:"CRUD operations (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Connecting frontend to backend"},{id:"phase-5-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Database integration basics"}]}]},{id:"phase-6",title:"Data Storage & Offline Support",description:"Real mobile apps must work even without internet. This phase introduces local storage systems and secure device-level persistence techniques.",topics:[{id:"phase-6-topic-1",title:"Storage Options",subtopics:[{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-1",title:"AsyncStorage"},{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-2",title:"SecureStore (secure data handling)"},{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-3",title:"SQLite (local database)"},{id:"phase-6-topic-1-sub-4",title:"FileSystem (file handling)"}]}]},{id:"phase-7",title:"Sensors & Motion",description:"This phase explores device hardware capabilities that make mobile apps interactive and context-aware.",topics:[{id:"phase-7-topic-1",title:"Expo Sensors",subtopics:[{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-1",title:"Expo Sensors overview"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Accelerometer → Tilt-based game"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Gyroscope → 3D Card Effect"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Magnetometer → Compass App"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-5",title:"Light Sensor → Auto Theme Switcher"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-6",title:"Pedometer → Step Counter"},{id:"phase-7-topic-1-sub-7",title:"DeviceMotion → Shake Detection"}]}]},{id:"phase-8",title:"Camera, Media & Audio",description:"Mobile devices provide powerful media capabilities. In this phase, you'll integrate camera, audio and media features into real applications.",topics:[{id:"phase-8-topic-1",title:"Media APIs",subtopics:[{id:"phase-8-topic-1-sub-1",title:"Expo Camera"},{id:"phase-8-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Audio recording & playback"},{id:"phase-8-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Media Library"}]}]},{id:"phase-9",title:"Device & System APIs",description:"This phase introduces deeper integrations with system-level APIs that enable richer application behavior.",topics:[{id:"phase-9-topic-1",title:"System APIs",subtopics:[{id:"phase-9-topic-1-sub-1",title:"Location (expo-location)"},{id:"phase-9-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Network state (expo-network)"},{id:"phase-9-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Battery status (expo-battery)"},{id:"phase-9-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Haptics (expo-haptics)"},{id:"phase-9-topic-1-sub-5",title:"File handling (document picker)"},{id:"phase-9-topic-1-sub-6",title:"Contacts access"}]}]},{id:"phase-10",title:"Expo Application Services (EAS)",description:"Now that apps are feature-complete, this phase prepares them for real-device testing and production build workflows.",topics:[{id:"phase-10-topic-1",title:"EAS",subtopics:[{id:"phase-10-topic-1-sub-1",title:"What is EAS & why it matters"},{id:"phase-10-topic-1-sub-2",title:"Expo Go vs Dev Builds"},{id:"phase-10-topic-1-sub-3",title:"Creating custom dev builds"},{id:"phase-10-topic-1-sub-4",title:"Running builds on real devices"},{id:"phase-10-topic-1-sub-5",t